NT|^b@2
After 1@H – 1@S – 2, a bid of 2@H by responder (North in this case) would be a sign-off on a poor hand, attempting to end the auction. 3@H is invitational (showing about 11 points or so) and is clearly non-forcing. (North was fully entitled to upgrade the @DK since we had bid the suit.) With a minimum hand we would have Passed 3@H, but with a robust opening bid we were fully entitled to have a dart at game.|
